cs.CV, cs.HC, cs.MM, cs.LG, cs.AI. 

The paper deals with computer vision and machine learning techniques to predict human focus of attention in RGBD videos. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also involves human-computer interaction (HCI) and multimedia (MM) aspects, which make cs.HC and cs.MM likely categories as well. The use of neural networks and deep learning techniques suggests that cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also a possible category. Finally, the paper involves the development of a new approach for video saliency estimation, which is a problem related to artificial intelligence (AI), making cs.AI a possible category as well.
